      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): treat block-boundary SSE events as liveness for idle timer",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nTreat block-boundary SSE events (`text_end`, `thinking_end`,\n`toolcall_start`, `toolcall_end`) as liveness signals that reset the\nidle timer, preventing premature stream abort when the model pauses at\nblock boundaries.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/opencode-go/stream-termination.ts`: Add 4 block-boundary\n  event types to `isProviderProgressEvent` so the idle timeout is reset\n  at block transitions.\n\n## Evidence\n\nBefore: Block-boundary SSE events did not reset the idle timer, causing\npremature abort on slow streams with quiet block transitions.\n\nAfter: The idle timer is reset at `text_end`, `thinking_end`,\n`toolcall_start`, and `toolcall_end` events, so the stream survives\nnormal block-boundary pauses.\n\n_AI-assisted._",
        "branch": "fix/issue-96518-Bug-opencode-go-stalled-str",
